title: What channel is Kansas City Royals-Toronto Blue Jays on? TV, live stream for ALCS Game 3
text:
What channel is Kansas City Royals-Toronto Blue Jays on? TV, live stream for ALCS Game 3 Salvador Perez, Wade Davis Kansas City Royals catcher Salvador Perez, left, and relief pitcher Wade Davis celebrate their 6-3 win over the Toronto Blue Jays in Game 2 of the American League Championship Series on Saturday in Kansas City. (Charlie Riedel | The Associated Press) 
The Toronto Blue Jays will try to get back in their American League Championship Series with Kansas City when they host the Royals at Rogers Centre in Game 3 tonight. 
Kansas City leads the best-of-7 series two games to none. 
Marcus Stroman will get the start for Toronto against the Royals' Johnny Cueto. 
The game starts at 8 p.m. and will be televised by Fox Sports 1. 
Here's how to find Fox Sports 1 in Central New York: Time Warner: Channel 400 (SD & HD) Verizon Fios: Channel 583 (HD) and 83 (SD) DirectTV: Channel 219 (SD & HD) Dish Network: Channel 150 (SD &HD) New Visions: Channel 768 (HD) and 83 (SD) 
You can also watch online or through tablets and mobile devices using FOX Sports GO .
